EDA Insights:

~2/3 are women.

~2/3 don't own a car.

~2/3 do own realty.

  • Majority of lessee's have Secondary or Higher Education.
  • Majority of Lessee's are married.
  • Over 90% live in homes (clearly since this dataset is over home loan defaults)
  • Majority of workers are laborers followed by sales staff.
  • Monday - Friday are when most loan processes are started, Saturday comes next, then Sunday lags behind. (Typical for regular business operating hours.)

2: Data Munging & Feature Selection¶

Due to the sheer number of features and Columns 44 through 90 are missing over 50% of their data I decided to remove those columns.

Suite_d = pd.DataFrame(pd.get_dummies(App_Red['NAME_TYPE_SUITE'])) 
Income_d = pd.DataFrame(pd.get_dummies(App_Red['NAME_INCOME_TYPE'])) 
Education_d = pd.DataFrame(pd.get_dummies(App_Red['NAME_EDUCATION_TYPE'])) 
Fam_d = pd.DataFrame(pd.get_dummies(App_Red['NAME_FAMILY_STATUS']))

from sklearn.ensemble import ExtraTreesClassifier
# Build a forest and compute the feature importances
import time
start_time = time.clock()
forest = ExtraTreesClassifier(n_estimators=250,
                              random_state=0)

forest.fit(ft_scale, target_train)
importances = forest.feature_importances_
std = np.std([tree.feature_importances_ for tree in forest.estimators_],
             axis=0)
indices = np.argsort(importances)[::-1]

# Print the feature ranking
print("Feature ranking:")

for f in range(ft_scale.shape[1]):
    print("%d. feature %d (%f)" % (f + 1, indices[f], importances[indices[f]]))

# Plot the feature importances of the forest
plt.figure()
plt.title("Feature importances")
plt.bar(range(ft_scale.shape[1]), importances[indices],
       color="r", yerr=std[indices], align="center")
plt.xticks(range(X.shape[1]), indices)
plt.xlim([-1, ft_scale.shape[1]])
plt.show()

print(time.clock() - start_time, "seconds")

# use a full grid over several parameters and cross validate 5 times
from sklearn.model_selection import GridSearchCV
#param_grid = {"alpha": [.01,.1, .5, 1, 2]}
param_grid={"n_neighbors": [10,15,1]} #this does a range 1 through 10 changes by a factor of 1. 
#param_grid={"n_neighbors": [10,15,1]} #this does a range 1 through 1 changes by a factor of .05

# run grid search
grid_search = GridSearchCV(neigh, param_grid=param_grid,n_jobs=-1,cv=5)
grid_search.fit(features_train, target_train)
print("Grid Scores", grid_search.cv_results_)
print("Best", grid_search.best_params_)

from sklearn.ensemble import AdaBoostClassifier
from sklearn.tree import DecisionTreeClassifier
import time
start_time = time.clock()
bdt = AdaBoostClassifier(DecisionTreeClassifier(max_depth=3),
                         algorithm="SAMME",
                         n_estimators=200)
bdt.fit(features_train, target_train)
predicted_bdt=bdt.predict(features_test)
expected = target_test
print(time.clock() - start_time, "seconds")
print("Adaboost Accuracy, DT, MD = 3, N = 200, Algorithm = SAMME", accuracy_score(expected,predicted_bdt))
print(classification_report(expected, predicted_bdt,target_names=['No', 'Yes']))
print(confusion_matrix(expected, predicted_bdt))
print('Area under the ROC Curve')
target_predicted_bdt_prob = bdt.predict_proba(features_test)
roc_auc_score(target_test, target_predicted_bdt_prob[:, 1])

from sklearn.ensemble import AdaBoostClassifier
from sklearn.tree import DecisionTreeClassifier
import time
start_time = time.clock()
bdt = AdaBoostClassifier(RandomForestClassifier(max_depth=3),
                         algorithm="SAMME",
                         n_estimators=100)
bdt.fit(features_train, target_train)
predicted_bdt=bdt.predict(features_test)
expected = target_test
print(time.clock() - start_time, "seconds")
print("Adaboost Accuracy, RF, MD = 3, N = 100, Algorithm = SAMME", accuracy_score(expected,predicted_bdt))
print(classification_report(expected, predicted_bdt,target_names=['No', 'Yes']))
print(confusion_matrix(expected, predicted_bdt))

# BEST MODEL
from sklearn.ensemble import GradientBoostingClassifier
import time
start_time = time.clock()
clf_GBC = GradientBoostingClassifier(n_estimators=200, learning_rate=0.7, max_depth=1, random_state=0, criterion = "mse")
clf_GBC.fit(features_train, target_train)
predicted_GBC=clf_GBC.predict(features_test)
expected = target_test
print(time.clock() - start_time, "seconds")
print("Gradient Boost Accuracy", accuracy_score(expected,predicted_GBC))
print(classification_report(expected, predicted_GBC,target_names=['No', 'Yes']))
print(confusion_matrix(expected, predicted_GBC))
print('Area under the ROC Curve')
target_predicted_clf_GBC_prob = clf_GBC.predict_proba(features_test)
roc_auc_score(target_test, target_predicted_clf_GBC_prob[:, 1])

                         algorithm="SAMME.R", learning_rate = 0.1,
                         n_estimators=10)
